    <div class="mx-auto max-w-prose space-y-16 leading-relaxed">
      <h3 class="text-f-xl mx-3 my-5 text-center font-display font-bold">
        Design
      </h3>
      <p
        class="first-letter:text-f-lg first-letter:font-semibold first-letter:text-geraldine-500"
      >
        Underneath are a few modern concepts generally used in web design
        process. These established standards and practices will offer you an
        insight into what exactly is included in my web design services.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="ph:globe-hemisphere-west-fill"
            class="flex flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400"
          />
          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Web Standards</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          Web standards are the formal, non-proprietary standards and other
          technical specifications that define and describe aspects of the World
          Wide Web.
        </p>
        <p>
          Web standards, in the narrow sense, consist of the following:
          Recommendations published by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C), such
          as HTML, Cascading Style Sheets, the Document Object Model, image
          formats like Portable Network Graphics and Scalable Vector Graphics.
          My process includes these standardized best practices.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="bx:expand-alt"
            class="flex items-center flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400"
          />
          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Responsive</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          Responsive web design is an approach to web design that makes web
          pages render properly on a variety of devices and window or screen
          sizes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your website will be crafted to provide an optimal viewing experience,
          easy reading and navigation with a minimum of re-sizing, panning, and
          scrolling across a broad range of devices (from mobile phones to
          desktop computer monitors).
        </p>
        <p>Want to see it live in action? Try re-sizing your browser window!</p>
        <img
          class="dark:brightness-75 dark:contrast-125 dark:filter"
          src={responsive}
          alt="Responsive"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="bx:check-shield"
            class="flex items-center flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-green-600 dark:text-green-400"
          />
          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Compatibility</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          Clean coding. Your website will function properly in all popular and
          latest browsers. I perform a cross-platform testing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="bx:accessibility"
            class="flex items-center flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-lime-600 dark:text-lime-400"
          />

          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Accessibility</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          A website that is accessible is designed to function properly with
          assistive technologies so that the information and functionality that
          is fundamental to the website is made accessible to every visitor. I
          use a variety of tools to audit my websites and that also includes
          testing it against the web accessibility guidelines defined by W3C.
        </p>

        <p>
          <Link href="/data/weboreviews.com-11.04.2022.pdf" target="_blank"
            >Accessibility audit</Link
          >
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="bx:mail-send"
            class="flex items-center flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-400"
          />

          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Contact Form</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          You will be provided a contact form with custom form fields, so your
          customers can contact you and provide information that
          <strong>you</strong> need.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <Icon
            name="bx:moon"
            class="flex items-center flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 mx-2 my-2 text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400"
          />

          <h4 class="text-f-lg font-display font-semibold">Dark mode</h4>
        </div>
        <p>
          The dark mode is a color scheme that uses light-colored text, icons
          and graphical user interface elements on a dark background. It reduces
          strain on your eyes and is very popular among all users. You can try
          seeing this website in dark mode if you haven't already. Use the theme
          button in the menu.
        </p>
      </div>

